{
  "text": "Of particular interest was the apparently critical transition in spoken word recognition between 19 and 12 visemes. The data from [CITATION_1] study of visually transcribed lexicons implies that some major changes occur between these two levels, with the number of unique words dropping rapidly after the 19 viseme level. It will be interesting to test in the future whether the effects found here over this transition are based on the properties of visually transcribed lexicons, and whether these properties have other effects on speechread spoken word recognition.",
  "citation_candidates": [
